information: LANDA is an independent family-run business set up in 1983 that specializes in the distribution of wearing and maintenance parts for agricultural harvesting machinery. LANDA supplies agricultural spare parts for harvesting equipment for a wide range of machines: forage choppers, combine harvesters, mowers, bale presses, self-propelled farming vehicles, etc. The firm positions itself as the contact to go to for distributors, entrepreneurs and farmers in the agricultural spare parts distribution value chain. LANDA distributes alternative parts, OEM parts and genuine replacement parts. The range of OEM parts come from the major global manufacturers, that are the references used for the initial assembly by most of the major machinery manufacturers such as CLAAS, JOHN DEERE, CNH and AGCO. Finally, in order to provide a global procurement solution for its customers, LANDA also carries genuine farming machinery parts. LANDA commits itself to users of agricultural harvesting machinery as a close partner, by offering a cost-effective and technical alternative to meet its customers' harvesting campaigns.
